                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 25: Companies can treat expenditure incurred on participating in auto expos and other exhibitions as business expenses and claim tax benefits, the Income Tax Appellate Tribunal said in a recent decision. The tribunal said expenditures on exhibitions are aimed to propagate business and hence cannot be disallowed for claiming tax benefits by the tax department. The case pertains to the participation of Austrian firm Styler India, within months of formation, in Auto Expo 1998, on which the company spent about Rs 15 lakh.                            
	 Mumbai, May 25: The RBI is likely to come out with guidelines on foreign currency exchangeable bonds (FCEBs) within a month. FCEBs are financial instruments similar to foreign currency convertible bonds and allow companies to raise money from overseas markets.                            
	 New Delhi, May 25: BSNL was the top revenue-earning telecom firm for the quarter ended March 2008 with its topline touching Rs 10,747.79 crore followed by Sunil Mittals Bharti at Rs 8,381 crore.                            
	 Mumbai, May 25: The Indian Banks Association and bank unions have called a meeting on June 9 in Calcutta to discuss the observations of the two actuaries appointed to assess the additional cost involved in providing a second pension option to bank employees.                            
	 nagpur, may 25: Minister of state for coal santosh bagrodia today said the coal ministry would not increase the prices of coal in view of already soaring prices of essential commodities.                                                                                                                          
